parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent ABS and Brake Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) and brake lights can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights come on randomly
stay on for varying lengths of time
and then shut off again. The lights may come on when the vehicle is in motion or when it's stopped. In some cases
the brakes may feel spongy or soft
or the vehicle may experience a loss of brake function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floorboard when depressed
and the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured rear axle can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds or vibrations from the rear of the vehicle
smoke coming from the rear tires
rear wheels leaning inward or rubbing against the body
and difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the subframe can cause the engine to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Abnormal noise from the front or rear of the vehicle
clunking noise
vibration
and rust or corrosion on the subframe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the rear axle can cause the axle to break, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Abnormal noise from the rear of the vehicle
vibration
and rust or corrosion on the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the frame to weaken, leading to loss of structural integrity and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame
holes in the frame
and abnormal noise from the front or rear of the vehicle.
